WEBVTT

00:06.482 --> 00:10.479
Fasting from sunrise to sunset every day is a crucial part of Ramadan,...

00:10.811 --> 00:13.055
...the annual, monthlong Muslim celebration...

00:13.187 --> 00:16.608
...that marks Allah's revelation of the Koran to the prophet Muhammad.

00:17.061 --> 00:19.195
These tips will help you stay strong throughout.

00:20.453 --> 00:26.219
You will need: A Muslim calendar, nutritious foods, self-discipline and charitable acts.

00:27.215 --> 00:30.557
Step 1: Ramadan's start date differs from year to year,...

00:30.876 --> 00:33.595
...so consult your local mosque or a reputable website...

00:33.705 --> 00:37.255
...to find out what day and at what time it begins in your area.

00:38.054 --> 00:41.142
Those exempt from fasting include children under age 12;...

00:41.523 --> 00:45.054
...menstruating, pregnant, and breastfeeding women; the frail and elderly;...

00:45.331 --> 00:48.055
...those who are not capable of understanding why they're fasting,...

00:48.468 --> 00:51.977
...and people whose health would be compromised by fasting, like diabetics.

00:52.639 --> 00:57.415
Step 2: Starting the night before the first fast day, and every night thereafter...

00:57.512 --> 01:00.415
...during the monthlong holiday, drink plenty of liquids.

01:00.797 --> 01:04.498
Food and beverages are prohibited from sunrise to sunset during Ramadan;...

01:04.969 --> 01:06.683
...this will help you stay hydrated.

01:07.481 --> 01:12.894
Step 3: Eat a balanced pre-sunrise meal, often known as "Suhoor" or "Sehri",...

01:13.189 --> 01:15.169
...to prepare your body for a day of fasting.

01:15.496 --> 01:20.689
Include whole grains like whole wheat bread or oatmeal; a protein like eggs or yogurt;...

01:21.064 --> 01:24.937
...a healthy fat such as nuts or an avocado, and some fresh fruit.

01:25.731 --> 01:29.389
Step 4: Say the appropriate prayers and begin fasting...

01:29.488 --> 01:32.046
...when the sky first starts to lighten on the horizon.

01:32.480 --> 01:37.729
Smoking, using perfume, and having sexual relations are also forbidden from sunup to sundown.

01:38.297 --> 01:42.035
Avoid strenuous exercise while fasting so you don't become dehydrated.

01:42.327 --> 01:45.809
If you have a regular fitness routine, cut down on the intensity and duration.

01:46.102 --> 01:49.396
Step 5: Use your extra free time for charitable acts,...

01:49.627 --> 01:52.194
...reading the Koran and performing daily prayers.

01:52.423 --> 01:56.956
Step 6: Break your fast at sunset with the meal known as "iftar."

01:57.396 --> 02:00.005
Say the appropriate prayers then start out slowly...

02:00.159 --> 02:03.003
...with a sip of water or milk, and a date or other fruit.

02:03.355 --> 02:07.351
Eat a variety of healthy foods to ensure that you're getting enough nutrients.

02:07.963 --> 02:09.629
Don't stuff yourself at sunset.

02:09.967 --> 02:13.586
Eating a few mini meals throughout the evening is better for your digestive system.

02:14.162 --> 02:19.005
Step 7: Repeat for the remainder of Ramadan, which lasts 29 to 30 days.

02:19.237 --> 02:22.219
End with the three-day celebration known as Eid al-Fitr,...

02:22.519 --> 02:26.291
...during which fasting is "forbidden" and the wearing of new clothes is encouraged.

02:26.749 --> 02:27.305
Did you know?

02:27.685 --> 02:33.413
Because the Muslim calendar follows the cycles of the moon, years are only 354 days long,...

02:33.694 --> 02:37.429
...and the months pass through all the seasons every 32 and a half years.

